<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFFBFFC4FF71FC25FA86FBD3" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFBFFC4FF71FC25FD6FFBBF" blockId="19.[151,1437,978,1149]" box="[151,658,1014,1041]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFFBFFC4FF79FC25FF05FBBF" box="[159,248,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="66.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[210,1376,198,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-32@66.[201,1387,181,1952]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="FIGURE 13. Southeast Asian Eudocima and Eudocima sikhimensis group adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605531" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605531/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs 13</figureCitation>
: G–H, 20: K, 26: F–H, 32: C, 95: D)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFBFFC4FF71FBC9FA86FBD3" blockId="19.[151,1437,978,1149]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
It is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FE40FBC9FDB4FB9A" box="[422,585,1051,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mionopasta">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FE40FBC9FDB4FB9A" box="[422,585,1051,1076]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. mionopasta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as described above. The forewings vary from pale yellowish green to deep green. The hindwing marginal band is disjunct from the outer margin but is broader than in similar and allopatric 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FA62FBEDFF16FBD2" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mazzeii">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FA62FBEDFF16FBD2" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. mazzeii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFBFFC4FEC4FBB1FE49FBD3" box="[290,436,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="behouneki">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFBFFC4FEC4FBB1FE49FBD3" box="[290,436,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">E. behouneki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The range includes the Indian Subregion, 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFBFFC4FC70FBB1FC01FBD3" box="[918,1020,1123,1149]" name="Thailand" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, and Sundaland (
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFFBFFC4FB5DFBB1FA8DFBD3" author="Holloway, J. D." box="[1211,1392,1122,1149]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 529" refId="ref38189" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2005) The moths of Borneo (parts 15 and 16): family Noctuidae, subfamily Catocalinae. Malayan Nature Journal, 59 (1 - 4), 1 - 529." type="journal article" year="2005">Holloway 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
